					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A treatise by Ḥayim Vital, with additions by other kabbalists.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Otsrot Ḥayim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אוצרות חיים</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains additions and glosses by Moses ben Mordecai Zacuto (marked as Kol Rama"z), Beyamin ha-Kohen and Nathan ben Reuben Shapira. The heading on folio 1 suggest that the work was written by a student of Nathan Shapira.</p>
								<p>Appended are: folio 226r - a diagram of ῾igulim; folio 227r - a diagram of sefirot; folio 228r - Seder ha-shemot shel ha-partsufim; folio 228v - Beḥinat nefesh, ruaḥ, neshamah; folio 231r - ῾Olam ha-beri᾿ah; folios 236v-237v - Madregot ha-shemot; folios 238v-239r - diagrams of sefirot; folio 240r - Keter penimi.</p>
							</note>
							<locus from="1r" to="240v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף, 1542-1620</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Otsrot_Hayim_1783"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
